On January 20, 2022, the President signed into law the Puerto Rico Recovery Accuracy in Disclosures Act of 2021 (PRRADA), also known as H.R. 1192. This law requires professionals involved in debt restructuring cases related to Puerto Rico to submit verified statements disclosing their connections with the debtor, creditors, and other interested parties before they can seek compensation for their services. The article also acknowledges the leadership of certain representatives and senators, including Velazquez, Briggs, Raskin, Grijalva, Cicilline, Jayapal, Gonzalez-Colon, Soto, Swalwell, Menendez, Hirono, Blumenthal, Rubio, Stabenow, Wicker, and Wyden.